# Test Coverage

- Every new or modified function, class, branch, and error path must have test coverage before finalizing changes.
- Add or update tests in the same language stack as the code (Python unit tests, Angular specs, etc.).
- Cover guard clauses, null/edge cases, and exception/error paths when logic branches are added.
- If behavior changes, update snapshots/integration baselines alongside unit tests where applicable.
- Treat uncovered touched files as incomplete work; either add tests or explicitly document and track as a blocker.
- Keep coverage-driven quality in mind: prioritize deterministic tests with no flaky dependencies.
